i was surprised that nimoy played a bad gud. he is best known for playing spock on star trek. if  they are all big names then why does the  movie get bad ratings
  EmprzAnastazia@... wrote:In a message dated 12/30/02 6:21:04 PM Central Standard Time, lordofdarkness11001@... writes:


robo i finally realized why kup is a good choice for an autobot 
becoming a member of a maximal. oh yeah remember when i said that 
there was a race on cybertron before the autobots and decipticons 
that race is the Quintessons. i watchedc tf the movie and was 
surprised when i saw tha leonard nimoy  played galvatron


o.O 
:: nods:: Nimoy was awesome as Galvatron. Notice that there are other big names in the movie.. Judd Nelson as Hot Rod, Robert Stack as Magnus, Lionel Stander as Kup, Eric Idle as Wreck Gar, Orson Wells as Unicron. Such a host of oustanding names in Hollywood. 
As to before the Qiunts, hard to say. However, the Quints were a part of Unicron's minons. A lot of the episodes being released inform alot of Transformer history now. "5 Faces of Darkness" is an excellent on informing the time of when the Quints governed Cybertron to how the Autobots & Decepticons came about & up to the present day. Awesome info in that episode if you ask me. 

Stac
